cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is about channel coding and decoding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed method involves integer programming and optimization, which are also relevant to computer science (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of heuristic algorithms and cuts suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.NE) may also be relevant sub-categories.
